        {
          "username": "Bertha Cruz",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "109716120507299989386",
          "user_review_count": 91,
          "user_photo_count": 374,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlamx60T4l_oDovIedHn5u6eKW1jxu_7ilqUsTyJ4p8I3vwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "My sister and I visited MedRite Tribeca Urgent Care-Manhattan today for bloodwork, and once again, the experience was exceptional. I\u2019ve been here before, but it was my sister\u2019s first time\u2014and she was just as impressed as I\u2019ve always been.  From the moment we walked in, the space felt clean, calm, and welcoming. The staff\u2019s empathy and kindness are truly unmatched. I\u2019ve come here during some of my most vulnerable moments while sick, and every time, I\u2019ve felt genuinely cared for.  Samantha, in particular, is a standout. Her bedside manner is impeccable\u2014she\u2019s kind, knowledgeable, thoughtful, professional, and incredibly empathetic. In a field as demanding as healthcare, having someone like her makes all the difference. I sincerely hope her journey continues to be fulfilling, because patients deserve to experience the kind of care she provides.\nMy sister had a similarly wonderful experience with Alicia, who was just as compassionate and attentive. Kudos to both of them for keeping patients at the heart of their work. Medical assistants like Samantha and Alicia remind us what true care looks like.  And a special shoutout to the receptionist\u2014we didn\u2019t catch her name, but she was phenomenal. I had a ton of questions, and her patience and helpfulness were on another level. Thank you, MedRite team, for consistently showing up with excellence and heart. You make healthcare feel human.",
